TITLE: Reusing Shared Windsor Container Across Reqnroll Scenarios (C#)
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to configure scenario-specific Windsor containers to inherit registrations from a pre-existing shared root container (`sharedRootContainer`). By setting the `Parent` property of the newly created container, shared services can be resolved from the root container, while scenario-scoped objects (like `ScenarioContext`) are resolved from the new child container. This promotes sharing of common, long-lived services across multiple scenarios.
SOURCE: https://github.com/reqnroll/reqnroll/blob/main/docs/integrations/windsor.md#2025-04-22_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: csharp
CODE:
```
[ScenarioDependencies]
public static IWindsorContainer CreateContainer()
{
  var container = new WindsorContainer();
  container.Parent = sharedRootContainer;

  return container;
}
```

